## Tool-routing quick reference

| Surface | Claude Code | GitHub Copilot |
|---|---|---|
| Skills install path | `.claude/skills/<name>/` | `.github/skills/<name>/` |
| Plan mode (interactive) | Yes | No (linear approval) |
| Multi-agent parallel | Yes (Agent tool) | Sequential subprocesses |
| PreToolUse hook | Yes | Yes (Preview) |

When in doubt: which tool's prompt did you type the slash into? That's
where the skill ran. There's no cross-tool dispatch.

---

## Troubleshooting

- **No `Next: /...` hint after a skill** → expected unless you've
  separately wired in optional Stop-hook support. This toolkit version
  doesn't install a Stop hook by default.
- **A skill's behavior doesn't match this map** → run `/cheatsheet
  <skill-name>` for the live SKILL.md. This template can drift; the
  SKILL.md files are authoritative.
- **`/sdlc` complains about missing config** → `.claude/project.json`
  needs `test.unit` (or whatever stage 5 references). Copy from
  `.claude/project.json.example` and fill in.
- **A new skill isn't in this map** → it landed after this template was
  generated. `/cheatsheet` will show it; edit this file to keep the map
  current.
